Alhaji Yakub Gobir, Waziri Kasar Hausa, and Madawaki of Ilorin on Sunday extended a congratulatory message to Muslim faithfuls in the country and Kwara State on the commencement of the Ramadan Fasting. In a press release he personally signed, the Chairman of Gobir Organization Foundation expressed gratitude to Almighty Allah while also supplicating for the forgiveness of sins and a rich reward for piety during the fasting period. He enjoined Muslim faithfuls to use this special period to call on Allah for protection, especially given the insecurity plaguing the country. “As we approach the 2023 election, let the wishes of the common men, women, and youth on the street be met,” he said.